						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Espozo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why in the world do you even have two different places you can jump to if there's not a single thing in between them?</div><br />Got ninjaed by NovaSquirrel. Anyways, I do the same thing quite often, and it's to help with code clarity and maintainability.<br /><br />Looks like there's a bug in that piece of code. <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">beq doneWallCollision</tt> never jumps since A was loaded with 28, but the <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">bcc notHitRight</tt> below it ends up picking up the slack. On top of that, I think it's a good practice to add a comment when you're purposefully using a conditional branch instruction for an unconditional branch, e.g. something like:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">bne doneWallCollision ; jumps always<br /></div><br /><br />...or just use BRA since we're on 65816 <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

					
